body:
The Dota 2 client is capable of streaming json updates about the game to an arbitrary HTTP endpoint, intended originally for applications like the [TI5 stage](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=elpIfQrKqrg) and LED-enabled peripherals.

`gogsi` listens to these updates and applies a user-defined callback to each one.

## Barebones Example

```go
package main

import "github.com/mammothbane/gogsi"

func main() {
	gogsi.Listen("localhost:3000", func(s *gogsi.State) error {
		if s.Added.Map.NightstalkerNight {
			/* adjust your phillips hue light, play a scary noise, update statistics, log something, etc. */
		}
		return nil
	})
}
```

### Credits
This package was inspired by [antonpup's C# implementation](https://github.com/antonpup/Dota2GSI).
